Tokyo today had the heaviest burst of
rain for a December day on record, according to the Japan
Meteorological Agency. As much as 29 millimeters of rain (1.2
inches) was recorded between 7:00 a.m. and 8:00 a.m. in the
cityâ€™s downtown Chiyoda ward, the agency said on its website.  The rain delayed or halted services on 17 train lines as of
